Two arrested after late night train brawlTWO people were arrested following a late night brawl on a Glasgow-bound train.A 24-year-old woman and a man, whose aged has not yet been revealed, were arrested in the incident.Police said another woman was allegedly attack on the Edinburgh Waverley to Garscadden train at around 11pm yesterday.The woman was allegedly assaulted as the train travelled through the Shettleston area.She is understood to have sustained a head injury during the incident.A BTP spokesman said: &quot;A man and a 24-year-old woman were arrested following a disturbance onboard an Edinburgh to Garscadden service in the Shettleston area around 11.00pm on Tuesday.&quot;Another woman was allegedly assaulted.&quot;The man and woman are due to appear at court later today.